0510: E8C2         ;--------------------------- Read Reader Byte - 3 (3) ----------------------;
0511: E8C2         ;   function reads the next character from the logical "reader" device into ;
0512: E8C2         ; register A. In practice, the physical device that is accessed depends     ;
0513: E8C2         ; entirely on how your BIOS is configured. In some systems, there is no     ;
0514: E8C2         ; reader at all; this function will return some arbitrary value such as lAH ;
0515: E8C2         ; (the ASCII CONTROL-Z character, used by CP/M to denote "End of File').    ;
0516: E8C2         ; Control is not returned to the calling program until a character has been ;
0517: E8C2         ; read.                                                                     ;
0518: E8C2         ;                                                                           ;
0519: E8C2         ; This is a blocking function                                               ;
0520: E8C2         ;																			;
0521: E8C2         ;			Function Code	:	C = 03H                                     ;
0522: E8C2         ;			Entry Parameters:	None										;
0523: E8C2         ;			Exit Parameters :	A = Character Input							;
0524: E8C2         ;																			;
0525: E8C2         ;--------------------------- Read Reader Byte - 3 (3) ----------------------;
0526: E8C2             vReaderIn:
0527: E8C2 CD 15 F6               CALL   bcReader
0528: E8C5 32 B6 EA               LD     (exitParameterWord),A
0529: E8C8 C9                     RET
0530: E8C9
0531: E8C9         ;--------------------------- Write Punch Byte - 4 (4) ----------------------;
0532: E8C9         ;  This function is a counterpart to the Read "Reader" Byte It outputs the  ;
0533: E8C9         ; specified character from register E to the logical punch device. Again,   ;
0534: E8C9         ; the actual physical device used, if any, is determined by the BIOS.       ;
0535: E8C9         ; There is no set standard for this device; in some systems the punch       ;
0536: E8C9         ; device is a "bit bucket," so called because it absorbs all data that you  ;
0537: E8C9         ; output to it.                                                             ;
0538: E8C9         ;																			;
0539: E8C9         ;			Function Code	:	C = 04H                                     ;
0540: E8C9         ;			Entry Parameters:	E = Data byte to be output					;
0541: E8C9         ;			Exit Parameters :	None										;
0542: E8C9         ;																			;
0543: E8C9         ;--------------------------- Write Punch Byte - 4 (4) ----------------------;
0544: E8C9         ;BDOS put parameter in C before entering this routine
0545: E8C9             vPunchOut:
0546: E8C9 CD 12 F6               CALL   bcPunch
0547: E8CC C9                     RET
