0640: E8F3         ;---------------------- Display $ terminated String - 9 (9) ----------------;
0641: E8F3         ;  This function outputs a string of characters to the console device. The  ;
0642: E8F3         ; address of this string is in registers DE. You must make sure that the    ;
0643: E8F3         ; last character of the string is "$"; the BDOS uses this character as a    ;
0644: E8F3         ; marker for the end of the string. The "$" itself does not get output to   ;
0645: E8F3         ; the console.                                                              ;
0646: E8F3         ;                                                                           ;
0647: E8F3         ; While the BDOS is outputting the string, it expands tabs as previously    ;
0648: E8F3         ; described, checks to see if there is an incoming character, and checks    ;
0649: E8F3         ; for  CONTROL-S (XOFF, which stops the output until another character is   ;
0650: E8F3         ; entered) or CONTROL-P (which turns on or off echoing of console characters;
0651: E8F3         ; to  the printer).                                                         ;
0652: E8F3         ;                                                                           ;
0653: E8F3         ;			Function Code	:	C = 09H                                     ;
0654: E8F3         ;			Entry Parameters:	DE = Address of the first byte of the string;
0655: E8F3         ;			Exit Parameters :	None							            ;
0656: E8F3         ;																			;
0657: E8F3         ;---------------------- Display $ terminated String - 9 (9) ----------------;
0658: E8F3             vPrintString:
0659: E8F3 2A B4 EA               LD     HL,(paramDE)         ; Get address of the string
0660: E8F6 4D                     LD     C,L
0661: E8F7 44                     LD     B,H                  ; Put it into BC for call
0662: E8F8 CD 3B E9               CALL   Print                ; out to console
0663: E8FB C9                     RET
0664: E8FC
0665: E8FC         ;-------------------------- Read Console String - A (10) -------------------;
0666: E8FC         ;  This function reads a string of characters from the console device       ;
0667: E8FC         ; and stores them in a buffer (address in DE) that you define. Full line    ;
0668: E8FC         ; editing is possible: the operator can backspace, cancel the line and      ;
0669: E8FC         ; start over, and use all the normal control functions. What you will       ;
0670: E8FC         ; ultimately see in the buffer is the final version of the character string ;
0671: E8FC         ; entered, without any of the errors or control characters used to do the   ;
0672: E8FC         ; line editing;                                                             ;
0673: E8FC         ;                                                                           ;
0674: E8FC         ;  The buffer that you define has a special format. The first byte in the   ;
0675: E8FC         ; buffer tells the BDOS the maximum number of characters to be accepted.    ;
0676: E8FC         ; The second byte is reserved for the BDOS to tell you how many characters  ;
0677: E8FC         ; were actually placed in the buffer. The following bytes contain           ;
0678: E8FC         ; the characters of the string. Character input will cease either when a    ;
0679: E8FC         ; CARRIAGE RETURN is entered or when the maximum number of characters,      ;
0680: E8FC         ; as specified in the buffer, has been received. The CARRIAGE RETURN is not ;
0681: E8FC         ; stored in the buffer as a character-it just serves as a terminator. If    ;
0682: E8FC         ; the first character entered is a CARRIAGE RETURN, then the BDOS sets      ;
0683: E8FC         ; the "characters input" byte to O. If you attempt to input more than the   ;
0684: E8FC         ; maximum number of characters, the "characters input" count will be the    ;
0685: E8FC         ; same as the maximum value allowed.                                        ;
0686: E8FC         ;                                                                           ;
0687: E8FC         ;			Function Code	:	C = 0AH                                     ;
0688: E8FC         ;			Entry Parameters:	DE = Address string buffer					;
0689: E8FC         ;			Exit Parameters :	String Buffer with console bytes in it      ;
0690: E8FC         ;																			;
0691: E8FC         ;-------------------------- Read Console String - A (10) -------------------;
0692: E8FC             vReadString:
0693: E8FC CD E0 E9               CALL   ReadString
0694: E8FF C9                     RET
