0712: E907         ;--------------------------- Get CP/M Version - C (12) ---------------------;
0713: E907         ;  This function tells you which version of CP/M you are currently running. ;
0714: E907         ; A two-byte value is returned:                                             ;
0715: E907         ;	H = OOH for CP/M, H = OlH for MP/M                                      ;
0716: E907         ;	L = OOH for all releases before CP/M 2.0                                ;
0717: E907         ;	L = 20H for CP/M 2.0,21 H for 2.1, 22H for 2.2,                         ;
0718: E907         ;		and so on for any subsequent releases.                              ;
0719: E907         ;                                                                           ;
0720: E907         ; This information is of interest only if your program has some version     ;
0721: E907         ; specific logic built into it. For example, CP/M version 1.4 does not      ;
0722: E907         ; support the same Random File Input/ Output operations that CP/M 2.2 does. ;
0723: E907         ; Therefore, if your program uses Random I/O, put this check at the         ;
0724: E907         ; beginning to ensure that it is indeed running under the appropriate       ;
0725: E907         ; version of CP/M.                                                          ;
0726: E907         ;                                                                           ;
0727: E907         ;			Function Code	:	C = 0CH                                     ;
0728: E907         ;			Entry Parameters:	None										;
0729: E907         ;			Exit Parameters :	HL =Version Number Code						;
0730: E907         ;								A = FFH	if incoming Data					;
0731: E907         ;																			;
0732: E907         ;--------------------------- Get CP/M Version - C (12) ---------------------;
0733: E907             vGetVersion:                      ; func12 (12 - 0C)	 Get Version
0734: E907 3E 20                  LD     A,VERSION
0735: E909 32 B6 EA               LD     (exitParameterByte),A ;exitParameterByte = VERSION
0736: E90C C9                     RET
