1171: EAB8         ; logical disks as having Read/Write status. The BDOS will then have to log ;
1172: EAB8         ; in each logical disk as each disk is accessed. This involves reading the  ;
1173: EAB8         ; entire file directory for the disk and rebuilding the allocation vectors  ;
1174: EAB8         ; which keep track of which allocation blocks are free and which            ;
1175: EAB8         ; are used for file storage.                                                ;
1176: EAB8         ;	Submit file is created by external command Submit. The file is          ;
1177: EAB8         ; identified as $$$.SUB                                                     ;
1178: EAB8         ;                                                                           ;
1179: EAB8         ;			Function Code	:	C = 0DH                                     ;
1180: EAB8         ;			Entry Parameters:	None										;
1181: EAB8         ;			Exit Parameters :	A = 00H if no Submit File found				;
1182: EAB8         ;								  = 0FFH if Submit file found				;
