1196: EAD1         ;---------------------------- Select Disk - E (14) -------------------------;
1197: EAD1         ;  This function makes the logical disk named in register E the default disk;
1198: EAD1         ; All subsequent references to disk files that do not specify the disk will ;
1199: EAD1         ; use this default. When you reference a disk file that does have an        ;
1200: EAD1         ; explicit logical disk in its name you do not have to issue another        ;
1201: EAD1         ; Select Disk function; the BDOS will take care of that for you.            ;
1202: EAD1         ;                                                                           ;
1203: EAD1         ;  Notice the way in which the logical disk is specified in register E.     ;
1204: EAD1         ; It is not the same as the disk drive specification in the first byte of   ;
1205: EAD1         ; the file control block. In the FeB, a value ofOOH is used to mean         ;
1206: EAD1         ; "use the current default disk" (as specified in the last Select Disk      ;
1207: EAD1         ; call or by the operator on the console). With this function, a value      ;
1208: EAD1         ; of OOH in register A means that A is the selected drive, a value of       ;
1209: EAD1         ; 01H means drive B, and so on to OFR for drive P, allowing                 ;
1210: EAD1         ; 16 drives in the system.                                                  ;
1211: EAD1         ;                                                                           ;
1212: EAD1         ;			Function Code	:	C = 0EH                                     ;
1213: EAD1         ;			Entry Parameters:	E = Logical Disk Code (00H = A,01H = B ..)	;
1214: EAD1         ;			Exit Parameters :	None										;
1215: EAD1         ;																			;
1216: EAD1         ;---------------------------- Select Disk - E (14) -------------------------;
1217: EAD1
1218: EAD1             vSelectDisk:
1219: EAD1 C3 12 ED               JP     SelectCurrent
