1706: EC35         ; (in the second 16 bytes).                                                 ;
1707: EC35         ;  This function returns a normal directory code if the file rename was     ;
1708: EC35         ; completed successfully or a value of OFFH if the old file name could not  ;
1709: EC35         ; be found.                                                                 ;
1710: EC35         ;                                                                           ;
1711: EC35         ;  The Rename File function only checks that the old file name and type     ;
1712: EC35         ; exist; it makes no check to ensure that the new name and type combination ;
1713: EC35         ; does not already exist. Therefore, you should try to open the new file    ;
1714: EC35         ; name and type. If you succeed, do not attempt the rename operation.       ;
1715: EC35         ; CP/M will create more than one file of the same name and type, and you    ;
1716: EC35         ; stand to lose the information in both files as you attempt to sort out    ;
1717: EC35         ; the problem.                                                              ;
