1847: EC7C         ;                                                                           ;
1848: EC7C         ;  Once you have requested Read-Only status for the currently selected      ;
1849: EC7C         ; logical disk, this status will persist even if you proceed to select      ;
1850: EC7C         ; other logical disks. In fact, it will remain in force until the next warm ;
1851: EC7C         ; boot or Reset Disk System function call.                                  ;
1852: EC7C         ;  Digital Research documentation refers to this function code as Disk Write;
1853: EC7C         ; Protect. The Read-Only description is used here because it corresponds    ;
1854: EC7C         ; to the error message produced if your program attempts to write on        ;
1855: EC7C         ; the disk.                                                                 ;
1856: EC7C         ;                                                                           ;
