2038: ECB3         ; used to position to the required place in the file, which can then be     ;
2039: ECB3         ; accessed sequentially.                                                    ;
2040: ECB3         ;                                                                           ;
2041: ECB3         ;  In order to use the Write Random, you must first open the base extent    ;
2042: ECB3         ; (extent 0) of the file. Even though there may be no data records in this  ;
2043: ECB3         ; extent, opening permits the file to be processed correctly.               ;
2044: ECB3         ;  As explained in the notes for the Read Random function, you can easily   ;
2045: ECB3         ; create a random file with gaps in it. If you were to create a file with   ;
2046: ECB3         ; record number 0 and record number 5000, there would be no intervening     ;
2047: ECB3         ; file extents.                                                             ;
2048: ECB3         ;                                                                           ;
2049: ECB3         ;			Function Code	:   C  = 24H                                    ;
2050: ECB3         ;			Entry Parameters:  DE = Address of File Control Block			;
