2066: ECBF         ;------------------------- Get File Size - 23 (35) -------------------------;
2067: ECBF         ;  This function returns the virtual size of the specified file. It does so ;
2068: ECBF         ; by setting the random record number (bytes 33-35) in the specified FCB to ;
2069: ECBF         ; the maximum 128-byte record number in the file. The virtual file size is  ;
2070: ECBF         ; calculated from the record address of the record following the end of the ;
2071: ECBF         ; file. Bytes 33 and 34 form a 16-bit value that contains the record number,;
2072: ECBF         ; with overflow indicated in byte 35. If byte 35 is 01, this means that the ;
2073: ECBF         ; file has the maximum record count of 65,536.                              ;
2074: ECBF         ;  If the function cannot find the file specified by the FCB, it returns    ;
2075: ECBF         ; with the random record field set to O.                                    ;
